00:53:24.000 --> 00:53:28.000
 Well, the trouble with Cytomel is that it's very fast acting.

00:53:28.000 --> 00:53:39.000
 For example, if I'm writing and I can't remember someone's name, I'll pick up a five microgram chip of Cytomel and chew it up.

00:53:39.000 --> 00:53:45.000
 And in about three or four or five minutes, I can remember anyone's name that I want to.

00:53:45.000 --> 00:53:48.000
 Almost instantaneous when you chew it.

00:53:48.000 --> 00:54:02.000
 It peaks after an hour and a half and starts down. When I took my whole day's allotment of, I think, was 25 micrograms of Cytomel in the morning by sunset.

00:54:02.000 --> 00:54:08.000
 After doing that for a few weeks by sunset, I was having hypothyroid arrhythmia.

00:54:08.000 --> 00:54:14.000
 My heart would stop every six seconds or so for about a second or two too long.

00:54:14.000 --> 00:54:26.000
 And when it would start doing that, it reminded me of several old people that I knew who had that kind of arrhythmia, a pause of a few seconds every several seconds.

00:54:26.000 --> 00:54:34.000
 I found that just by chewing up a 10 microgram Cytomel, my heart rhythm would immediately be restored.

00:54:34.000 --> 00:54:38.000
 A thyroid supplement had the same effect in some of my old friends.

00:54:38.000 --> 00:54:45.000
 Within an hour, their pauses would quit. They would have a perfectly regular heartbeat.

00:54:45.000 --> 00:54:58.000
 And if they kept that up, that would cure their circulatory problems for foot gangrene and various other problems that simply resulted from hypothyroid for circulation.

