 It was the standard for all of the definitions of how thyroid works from about 1910 on.

00:55:11.000 --> 00:55:18.000
 But in the late 80s or early 90s, I think it was Revlon Company that bought the company from Armour.

00:55:18.000 --> 00:55:23.000
 And then it went through a couple of sales each time increasing the price.

00:55:23.000 --> 00:55:32.000
 But with the final owner, they decided to process the material more than the Armour Company had ever done.

00:55:32.000 --> 00:55:38.000
 The Armour Company tested every batch, whether it was beef or pork, glandular or a mixture.

00:55:38.000 --> 00:55:44.000
